  "body": "- [Yes] I've asked for help in the [Truffle Gitter](http://gitter.im/Consensys/truffle) before filing this issue.\r\n\r\n---------------------------\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\n\r\nJavaScript test in the form of \r\n\r\n        Dummy.deployed().then(function(instance) {\r\n            dummy = instance;\r\n            return web3.eth.getBalance(address);\r\n\r\n        }).then(function(balance) {\r\n            balance_before = balance;\r\n            console.log(\"Balance before:\", balance.toString());\r\n            return dummy.store({from: address, value: amount});\r\n\r\n        }).then(function(result) {\r\n            console.log(\"'store' transaction finished; tx=\", result.tx);\r\n        });\r\n        console.log(\"First test finished\");\r\n\r\nFinishes before all the futures are completed.\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\nDownload the attached toy example tarball and:\r\n\r\n    $ tar xf eth-dummy.tar.gz\r\n    $ cd eth-dummy\r\n    $ truffle develop\r\n    truffle(develop)> compile\r\n    truffle(develop)> test\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nFirst, all futures finishes, then the test itself finishes.\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\nTest finishes before all futures are completed. This is what I can see on my machine:\r\n\r\n```\r\neth-dummy$ truffle develop\r\nConnected to existing Truffle Develop session at http://localhost:9545/\r\n\r\ntruffle(develop)> compile\r\nCompiling ./contracts/Dummy.sol...\r\nCompiling ./contracts/Migrations.sol...\r\ntruffle(develop)> Writing artifacts to ./build/contracts\r\n\r\ntruffle(develop)> test\r\nUsing network 'develop'.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n  Contract: Dummy\r\nFirst test finished\r\n    âœ“ Should send and get 10 Ether\r\nBalance before: 59420666200000000000\r\n\r\n\r\n  1 passing (205ms)\r\n\r\ntruffle(develop)> 'store' transaction finished; tx= 0x9eb93861f0a70155fb6700d777a443796fb9d6a00cc115f2959a45170aa3c0b7\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: Fedora 27\r\n* Truffle version: Truffle v4.0.1 (core: 4.0.1), Solidity v0.4.18 (solc-js)\r\n* Ethereum client: truffle develop\r\n* node version: N/A\r\n* npm version: 5.5.1\r\n[eth-dummy.tar.gz](https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/files/1553111/eth-dummy.tar.gz)\r\n\r\n",
